Program: The Why Factor
Title: Laziness
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csvtcf
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 25 Mar 2018
Laziness, slothfulness, idleness and apathy are used as criticisms and insults against individuals, groups and sometimes whole countries. But why? The Greeks saw laziness as a virtue and something to be sought after whereas today we look down on being unproductive. Should we keep ourselves constantly busy or is laziness something we should feel less guilty about? Isnâ€™t a little bit of downtime good for the soul? After all, do good things not come out of taking it easy? (Photo: Legs extended on a hammock. Credit: Shutterstock) Show less